Even though the script below sorts the list of integers, it's not very efficient.
Here is a more efficient sort algorithm in Python:
```
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n-1):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
```
This algorithm swaps the adjacent elements if they are not in order. The advantage of this algorithm over the previous one is that it only swaps the elements if they are out of order, rather than swapping every element with every other element.

